18/*
19 * Scripts for spells with SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC which cannot be included in AI script file
20 * of creature using it or can't be bound to any player class.
21 * Ordered alphabetically using scriptname.
22 * Scriptnames of files in this file should be prefixed with "spell_gen_"
23 */
24

52// 46642 - 5,000 Gold
53class spell_gen_5000_gold : public SpellScript
54{
55 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_5000_gold);
56
57 void HandleScript(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
58 {
59 if (Player* target = GetHitPlayer())
60 {
61 target->ModifyMoney(5000 * GOLD);
62 }
63 }
64
65 void Register() override
66 {
67 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_5000_gold::HandleScript, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
68 }
69};

71// 24401 - Test Pet Passive
72class spell_gen_model_visible : public AuraScript
73{
74public:
75 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_model_visible)
76
77 bool Load() override
78 {
79 _modelId = 0;
80 _hasFlag = false;
81 return true;
82 }
83
84 void HandleEffectApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
85 {
86 _modelId = GetUnitOwner()->GetDisplayId();
87 _hasFlag = GetUnitOwner()->HasUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE);
88 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
89 _itemId.at(i) = GetUnitOwner()->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + i);
90
91 GetUnitOwner()->SetDisplayId(11686);
92 GetUnitOwner()->SetUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE);
93 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
94 GetUnitOwner()->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + i, 0);
95 }
96
97 void HandleEffectRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
98 {
99 GetUnitOwner()->SetDisplayId(_modelId);
100 if (!_hasFlag)
101 GetUnitOwner()->RemoveUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE);
102 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
103 GetUnitOwner()->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + i, _itemId.at(i));
104 }
105
106 void Register() override
107 {
108 OnEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_model_visible::HandleEffectApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
109 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_model_visible::HandleEffectRemove, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
110 }
111
112private:
113 std::array<uint32, 3> _itemId = { {0, 0, 0} };
114 uint32 _modelId;
115 bool _hasFlag;
116};

118// 51640 - Taunt Flag Targeting
119class spell_the_flag_of_ownership : public SpellScript
120{
121 PrepareSpellScript(spell_the_flag_of_ownership);
122
123 bool haveTarget;
124 bool Load() override
125 {
126 haveTarget = false;
127 return true;
128 }
129
130 void HandleScript(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
131 {
132 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
133 if (!caster || caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
134 return;
135 Player* target = GetHitPlayer();
136 if (!target)
137 return;
138 caster->CastSpell(target, 52605, true);
139 char buff[100];
140 sprintf(buff, "%s plants the Flag of Ownership in the corpse of %s.", caster->GetName().c_str(), target->GetName().c_str());
141 caster->TextEmote(buff, caster);
142 haveTarget = true;
143 }
144
145 void FilterTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets)
146 {
147 for( std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); )
148 {
149 if ((*itr)->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || (*itr)->ToPlayer()->IsAlive())
150 {
151 targets.erase(itr);
152 itr = targets.begin();
153 continue;
154 }
155 ++itr;
156 }
157 }
158
159 void HandleFinish()
160 {
161 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
162 if (!caster || !caster->ToPlayer())
163 return;
164
165 if (!haveTarget)
166 {
167 caster->ToPlayer()->RemoveSpellCooldown(GetSpellInfo()->Id, true);
168 Spell::SendCastResult(caster->ToPlayer(), GetSpellInfo(), 0, SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS);
169 }
170 }
171
172 void Register() override
173 {
174 AfterCast += SpellCastFn(spell_the_flag_of_ownership::HandleFinish);
175 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_the_flag_of_ownership::HandleScript, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY);
176 OnObjectAreaTargetSelect += SpellObjectAreaTargetSelectFn(spell_the_flag_of_ownership::FilterTargets, EFFECT_0, TARGET_CORPSE_SRC_AREA_ENEMY);
177 }
178};

180/* 51060 - Have Withered Batwing
181 51068 - Have Muddy Mire Maggot
182 51088 - Have Amberseed
183 51094 - Have Chilled Serpent Mucus */
184class spell_gen_have_item_auras : public AuraScript
185{
186 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_have_item_auras)
187
188 void HandleEffectApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
189 {
190 Unit* target = GetTarget();
191 if (target && target->ToPlayer())
192 {
193 uint32 entry = 0;
194 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
195 {
196 case 51060: // Have Withered Batwing
197 entry = 28294;
198 break;
199 case 51068: // Have Muddy Mire Maggot
200 entry = 28293;
201 break;
202 case 51094: // Have Chilled Serpent Mucus
203 entry = 28296;
204 break;
205 case 51088: // Have Amberseed
206 entry = 28295;
207 break;
208 }
209
210 if (entry)
211 target->ToPlayer()->KilledMonsterCredit(entry);
212 }
213 }
214
215 void Register() override
216 {
217 OnEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_have_item_auras::HandleEffectApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
218 }
219};

227/* 54355 - Detonation
228 57099 - Landmine Knockback Achievement Aura */
229class spell_gen_mine_sweeper : public SpellScript
230{
231 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_mine_sweeper);
232
233 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
234 {
235 return ValidateSpellInfo({ SPELL_LAND_MINE_KNOCKBACK, SPELL_LANDMINE_KNOCKBACK_ACHIEVEMENT});
236 }
237
238 void HandleSchoolDMG(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
239 {
240 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
241 Player* target = GetHitPlayer();
242 if (!target)
243 return;
244
245 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED);
246 caster->CastSpell(target, SPELL_LAND_MINE_KNOCKBACK, true);
247 }
248
249 void HandleScriptEffect(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
250 {
251 if (Unit* target = GetHitPlayer())
252 if (Aura* aur = target->GetAura(GetSpellInfo()->Id))
253 if (aur->GetStackAmount() >= 10)
254 target->CastSpell(target, SPELL_LANDMINE_KNOCKBACK_ACHIEVEMENT, true);
255 }
256
257 void Register() override
258 {
259 if (m_scriptSpellId == 54355)
260 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mine_sweeper::HandleSchoolDMG, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE);
261 else
262 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mine_sweeper::HandleScriptEffect, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
263 }
264};

266/* 20004 - Life Steal
267 20005 - Chilled
268 20007 - Holy Strength */
269class spell_gen_reduced_above_60 : public SpellScript
270{
271 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_reduced_above_60);
272
273 void RecalculateDamage()
274 {
275 if (Unit* target = GetHitUnit())
276 if (target->getLevel() > 60)
277 {
278 int32 damage = GetHitDamage();
279 AddPct(damage, -4 * int8(std::min(target->getLevel(), uint8(85)) - 60)); // prevents reduce by more than 100%
280 SetHitDamage(damage);
281 }
282 }
283
284 void Register() override
285 {
286 OnHit += SpellHitFn(spell_gen_reduced_above_60::RecalculateDamage);
287 }
288};
289
290class spell_gen_reduced_above_60_aura : public AuraScript
291{
292 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_reduced_above_60_aura);
293
294 void CalculateAmount(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
295 {
296 if (Unit* owner = GetUnitOwner())
297 if (owner->getLevel() > 60)
298 AddPct(amount, -4 * int8(std::min(owner->getLevel(), uint8(85)) - 60)); // prevents reduce by more than 100%
299 }
300
301 void Register() override
302 {
303 if (m_scriptSpellId != 20004) // Lifestealing enchange - no aura effect
304 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_gen_reduced_above_60_aura::CalculateAmount, EFFECT_ALL, SPELL_AURA_ANY);
305 }
306};

308/* 69664 - Aquanos Laundry (spell_q20438_q24556_aquantos_laundry)
309 38724 - Magic Sucker Device (Success Visual) (spell_q10838_demoniac_scryer_visual) */
310class spell_gen_relocaste_dest : public SpellScript
311{
312 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_relocaste_dest);
313public:
314 spell_gen_relocaste_dest(float x, float y, float z, float o) : _x(x), _y(y), _z(z), _o(o) { }
315
316 void RelocateDest()
317 {
318 Position const offset = {_x, _y, _z, _o};
319 const_cast<WorldLocation*>(GetExplTargetDest())->RelocateOffset(offset);
320 }
321
322 void Register() override
323 {
324 OnCast += SpellCastFn(spell_gen_relocaste_dest::RelocateDest);
325 }
326
327private:
328 float _x, _y, _z, _o;
329};

331/* 55640 - Lightweave Embroidery
332 67698 - Item - Coliseum 25 Normal Healer Trinket
333 67752 - Item - Coliseum 25 Heroic Healer Trinket
334 69762 - Unchained Magic */
335class spell_gen_allow_proc_from_spells_with_cost : public AuraScript
336{
337 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_allow_proc_from_spells_with_cost);
338
339 bool CheckProc(ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
340 {
341 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = eventInfo.GetSpellInfo();
342 if (!spellInfo)
343 return false;
344
345 // xinef: Spells with no damage class and physical school only are not treated as spells
346 if ((eventInfo.GetTypeMask() & (PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_NEG | PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_POS)) && spellInfo->SchoolMask == SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_NORMAL)
347 return false;
348
349 // xinef: holy nova exception
350 if (spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 1874)
351 return spellInfo->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL);
352
353 // xinef: Holy Shock exception...
354 return spellInfo->ManaCost > 0 || spellInfo->ManaCostPercentage > 0 || (spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 156);
355 }
356
357 void Register() override
358 {
359 DoCheckProc += AuraCheckProcFn(spell_gen_allow_proc_from_spells_with_cost::CheckProc);
360 }
361};

363/* 32727 - Arena Preparation
364 44521 - Preparation */
365class spell_gen_bg_preparation : public AuraScript
366{
367 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_bg_preparation)
368
369 void HandleEffectApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
370 {
371 GetTarget()->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_DAMAGE, SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_ALL, true);
372 }
373
374 void HandleEffectRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
375 {
376 GetTarget()->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_DAMAGE, SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_ALL, false);
377 }
378
379 void CalcPeriodic(AuraEffect const* /*effect*/, bool& isPeriodic, int32& amplitude)
380 {
381 isPeriodic = true;
382 amplitude = 3 * IN_MILLISECONDS;
383 }
384
385 void Update(AuraEffect* /*effect*/)
386 {
387 if (Player* player = GetUnitOwner()->GetCharmerOrOwnerPlayerOrPlayerItself())
388 if (MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(player->GetMapId()))
389 if ((GetId() == 32727 && mapEntry->IsBattleArena()) || (GetId() == 44521 && mapEntry->IsBattleground()))
390 if (Battleground* bg = player->GetBattleground())
391 if (bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_JOIN)
392 return;
393 SetMaxDuration(1);
394 SetDuration(1);
395 }
396
397 void Register() override
398 {
399 OnEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_bg_preparation::HandleEffectApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_COST_SCHOOL_PCT, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
400 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_bg_preparation::HandleEffectRemove, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_COST_SCHOOL_PCT, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
401
402 DoEffectCalcPeriodic += AuraEffectCalcPeriodicFn(spell_gen_bg_preparation::CalcPeriodic, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_COST_SCHOOL_PCT);
403 OnEffectUpdatePeriodic += AuraEffectUpdatePeriodicFn(spell_gen_bg_preparation::Update, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_COST_SCHOOL_PCT);
404 }
405};

407/* 27867 - Freeze (spell_gen_disabled_above_70)
408 59917 - Minor Mount Speed (spell_gen_disabled_above_70)
409 46629 - Deathfrost (spell_gen_disabled_above_73) */
410class spell_gen_disabled_above_level : public SpellScript
411{
412 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_disabled_above_level)
413
414public:
415 spell_gen_disabled_above_level(uint8 level) : SpellScript(), _level(level) { }
416
417 SpellCastResult CheckRequirement()
418 {
419 if (Unit* target = GetExplTargetUnit())
420 if (target->getLevel() >= _level)
421 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
422
423 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
424 }
425
426 void Register() override
427 {
428 OnCheckCast += SpellCheckCastFn(spell_gen_disabled_above_level::CheckRequirement);
429 }
430
431private:
432 uint8 _level;
433};

435/* 61013 - Warlock Pet Scaling 05
436 61017 - Hunter Pet Scaling 04 */
437class spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling : public AuraScript
438{
439 PrepareAuraScript(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling)
440
441 int32 CalculatePercent(float hitChance, float cap, float maxChance)
442 {
443 return (hitChance / cap) * maxChance;
444 }
445
446 void CalculateHitAmount(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
447 {
448 if (Player* modOwner = GetUnitOwner()->GetSpellModOwner())
449 {
450 if (modOwner->getClass() == CLASS_HUNTER)
451 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modRangedHitChance, 8.0f, 8.0f);
452 else if (modOwner->getPowerType() == POWER_MANA)
453 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modSpellHitChance, 17.0f, 8.0f);
454 else
455 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modMeleeHitChance, 8.0f, 8.0f);
456 }
457 }
458
459 void CalculateSpellHitAmount(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
460 {
461 if (Player* modOwner = GetUnitOwner()->GetSpellModOwner())
462 {
463 if (modOwner->getClass() == CLASS_HUNTER)
464 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modRangedHitChance, 8.0f, 17.0f);
465 else if (modOwner->getPowerType() == POWER_MANA)
466 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modSpellHitChance, 17.0f, 17.0f);
467 else
468 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modMeleeHitChance, 8.0f, 17.0f);
469 }
470 }
471
472 void CalculateExpertiseAmount(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
473 {
474 if (Player* modOwner = GetUnitOwner()->GetSpellModOwner())
475 {
476 if (modOwner->getClass() == CLASS_HUNTER)
477 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modRangedHitChance, 8.0f, 26.0f);
478 else if (modOwner->getPowerType() == POWER_MANA)
479 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modSpellHitChance, 17.0f, 26.0f);
480 else
481 amount = CalculatePercent(modOwner->m_modMeleeHitChance, 8.0f, 26.0f);
482 }
483 }
484
485 void HandleEffectApply(AuraEffect const* aurEff, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
486 {
487 GetUnitOwner()->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_STATE, aurEff->GetAuraType(), true, SPELL_BLOCK_TYPE_POSITIVE);
488 }
489
490 void CalcPeriodic(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, bool& isPeriodic, int32& amplitude)
491 {
492 if (!GetUnitOwner()->IsPet())
493 return;
494
495 isPeriodic = true;
496 amplitude = 3 * IN_MILLISECONDS;
497 }
498
499 void HandlePeriodic(AuraEffect const* aurEff)
500 {
501 PreventDefaultAction();
502 GetEffect(aurEff->GetEffIndex())->RecalculateAmount();
503 }
504
505 void Register() override
506 {
507 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling::CalculateHitAmount, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_HIT_CHANCE);
508 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling::CalculateSpellHitAmount, EFFECT_1, SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_HIT_CHANCE);
509 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling::CalculateExpertiseAmount, EFFECT_2, SPELL_AURA_MOD_EXPERTISE);
510
511 OnEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling::HandleEffectApply, EFFECT_ALL, SPELL_AURA_ANY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
512 DoEffectCalcPeriodic += AuraEffectCalcPeriodicFn(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling::CalcPeriodic, EFFECT_ALL, SPELL_AURA_ANY);
513 OnEffectPeriodic += AuraEffectPeriodicFn(spell_pet_hit_expertise_scalling::HandlePeriodic, EFFECT_ALL, SPELL_AURA_ANY);
514 }
515};

536// 22888 - Rallying Cry of the Dragonslayer
537class spell_gen_rallying_cry_of_the_dragonslayer : public SpellScript
538{
539 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_rallying_cry_of_the_dragonslayer);
540
541 void SelectTarget(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets)
542 {
543 targets.clear();
544
545 uint32 zoneId = 1519;
546 if (GetCaster()->GetMapId() == 1) // Kalimdor
547 zoneId = 1637;
548
549 Map::PlayerList const& pList = GetCaster()->GetMap()->GetPlayers();
550 for (Map::PlayerList::const_iterator itr = pList.begin(); itr != pList.end(); ++itr)
551 if (itr->GetSource()->GetZoneId() == zoneId)
552 targets.push_back(itr->GetSource());
553 }
554
555 void Register() override
556 {
557 OnObjectAreaTargetSelect += SpellObjectAreaTargetSelectFn(spell_gen_rallying_cry_of_the_dragonslayer::SelectTarget, EFFECT_ALL, TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ALLY);
558 }

602// 59630 - Black Magic
603class spell_gen_black_magic_enchant : public AuraScript
604{
605 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_black_magic_enchant);
606
607 bool CheckProc(ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
608 {
609 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = eventInfo.GetSpellInfo();
610 if (!spellInfo)
611 return false;
612
613 // Xinef: Old 'code'
614 if (eventInfo.GetTypeMask() & PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_NEG)
615 return true;
616
617 // Implement Black Magic enchant Bug
618 if (spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID)
619 if (spellInfo->SpellIconID == 2857 /*SPELL_INFECTED_WOUNDS*/ || spellInfo->SpellIconID == 147 /*SPELL_SHRED*/ || spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x400 /*SPELL_MANGLE_(CAT)*/)
620 return true;
621
622 return false;
623 }
624
625 void Register() override
626 {
627 DoCheckProc += AuraCheckProcFn(spell_gen_black_magic_enchant::CheckProc);
628 }
629};

1128 haunt->GetMotionMaster()->MoveFollow(caster, 1, M_PI);

1174enum AdaptiveWarding

1177 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_NATURE = 28768,
1178 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FROST = 28766,
1179 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_SHADOW = 28769,
1180 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_ARCANE = 28770
1181};
1182
1183// 28764 - Adaptive Warding (Frostfire Regalia Set)
1184class spell_gen_adaptive_warding : public AuraScript
1185{
1186 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_adaptive_warding);
1187
1188 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
1189 {
1190 return ValidateSpellInfo(
1191 {
1192 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FIRE,
1193 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_NATURE,
1194 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FROST,
1195 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_SHADOW,
1196 SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_ARCANE
1197 });
1198 }
1199
1200 bool CheckProc(ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1201 {
1202 if (!eventInfo.GetSpellInfo())
1203 return false;
1204
1205 // find Mage Armor
1206 if (!GetTarget()->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_MANA_REGEN_INTERRUPT, SPELLFAMILY_MAGE, 0x10000000, 0x0, 0x0))
1207 return false;
1208
1209 switch (GetFirstSchoolInMask(eventInfo.GetSchoolMask()))
1210 {
1211 case SPELL_SCHOOL_NORMAL:
1212 case SPELL_SCHOOL_HOLY:
1213 return false;
1214 default:
1215 break;
1216 }
1217 return true;
1218 }
1219
1220 void HandleProc(AuraEffect const* aurEff, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1221 {
1222 PreventDefaultAction();
1223
1224 uint32 spellId = 0;
1225 switch (GetFirstSchoolInMask(eventInfo.GetSchoolMask()))
1226 {
1227 case SPELL_SCHOOL_FIRE:
1228 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FIRE;
1229 break;
1230 case SPELL_SCHOOL_NATURE:
1231 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_NATURE;
1232 break;
1233 case SPELL_SCHOOL_FROST:
1234 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FROST;
1235 break;
1236 case SPELL_SCHOOL_SHADOW:
1237 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_SHADOW;
1238 break;
1239 case SPELL_SCHOOL_ARCANE:
1240 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_ARCANE;
1241 break;
1242 default:
1243 return;
1244 }
1245 GetTarget()->CastSpell(GetTarget(), spellId, true, nullptr, aurEff);
1246 }
1247
1248 void Register() override
1249 {
1250 DoCheckProc += AuraCheckProcFn(spell_gen_adaptive_warding::CheckProc);
1251 OnEffectProc += AuraEffectProcFn(spell_gen_adaptive_warding::HandleProc, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY);
1252 }
1253};
1254

1256 45823 - Tower Point Warmaster
1257 45824 - West Frostwolf Warmaster
1258 45826 - East Frostwolf Warmaster
1259 45828 - Dun Baldar North Marshal
1260 45829 - Dun Baldar South Marshal
1261 45830 - Stonehearth Marshal
1262 45831 - Icewing Marshal */

1312enum CannibalizeSpells
1313{
1314 SPELL_CANNIBALIZE_TRIGGERED = 20578
1315};
1316
1317// 20577 - Cannibalize
1318class spell_gen_cannibalize : public SpellScript
1319{
1320 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_cannibalize);
1321
1322 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
1323 {
1324 return ValidateSpellInfo({ SPELL_CANNIBALIZE_TRIGGERED });
1325 }
1326
1327 SpellCastResult CheckIfCorpseNear()
1328 {
1329 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
1330 float max_range = GetSpellInfo()->GetMaxRange(false);
1331 WorldObject* result = nullptr;
1332 // search for nearby enemy corpse in range
1333 Acore::AnyDeadUnitSpellTargetInRangeCheck check(caster, max_range, GetSpellInfo(), TARGET_CHECK_CORPSE);
1334 Acore::WorldObjectSearcher<Acore::AnyDeadUnitSpellTargetInRangeCheck> searcher(caster, result, check);
1335 Cell::VisitWorldObjects(caster, searcher, max_range);
1336 if (!result)
1337 {
1338 Cell::VisitGridObjects(caster, searcher, max_range);
1339 }
1340 if (!result)
1341 {
1342 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_EDIBLE_CORPSES;
1343 }
1344 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1345 }
1346
1347 void HandleDummy(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
1348 {
1349 GetCaster()->CastSpell(GetCaster(), SPELL_CANNIBALIZE_TRIGGERED, false);
1350 }
1351
1352 void Register() override
1353 {
1354 OnEffectHit += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_cannibalize::HandleDummy, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY);
1355 OnCheckCast += SpellCheckCastFn(spell_gen_cannibalize::CheckIfCorpseNear);
1356 }
1357};

1448enum Netherbloom
1449{
1450 SPELL_NETHERBLOOM_POLLEN_1 = 28703
1451};
1452
1453// 28702 - Netherbloom
1454class spell_gen_netherbloom : public SpellScript
1455{
1456 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_netherbloom);
1457
1458 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
1459 {
1460 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 5; ++i)
1461 if (!sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_NETHERBLOOM_POLLEN_1 + i))
1462 return false;
1463 return true;
1464 }
1465
1466 void HandleScript(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
1467 {
1468 PreventHitDefaultEffect(effIndex);
1469
1470 if (Unit* target = GetHitUnit())
1471 {
1472 // 25% chance of casting a random buff
1473 if (roll_chance_i(75))
1474 return;
1475
1476 // triggered spells are 28703 to 28707
1477 // Note: some sources say, that there was the possibility of
1478 // receiving a debuff. However, this seems to be removed by a patch.
1479
1480 // don't overwrite an existing aura
1481 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 5; ++i)
1482 if (target->HasAura(SPELL_NETHERBLOOM_POLLEN_1 + i))
1483 return;
1484
1485 target->CastSpell(target, SPELL_NETHERBLOOM_POLLEN_1 + urand(0, 4), true);
1486 }
1487 }
1488
1489 void Register() override
1490 {
1491 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_netherbloom::HandleScript, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
1492 }
1493};

1538// 27539 - Obsidian Armor
1539class spell_gen_obsidian_armor : public AuraScript
1540{
1541 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_obsidian_armor);
1542
1543 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
1544 {
1545 return ValidateSpellInfo(
1546 {
1547 SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_HOLY,
1548 SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_FIRE,
1549 SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_NATURE,
1550 SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_FROST,
1551 SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_SHADOW,
1552 SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_ARCANE
1553 });
1554 }
1555
1556 bool CheckProc(ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1557 {
1558 if (eventInfo.GetSpellInfo())
1559 {
1560 return false;
1561 }
1562
1563 if (GetFirstSchoolInMask(eventInfo.GetSchoolMask()) == SPELL_SCHOOL_NORMAL)
1564 return false;
1565
1566 return true;
1567 }
1568
1569 void OnProc(AuraEffect const* aurEff, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1570 {
1571 PreventDefaultAction();
1572
1573 uint32 spellId = 0;
1574 switch (GetFirstSchoolInMask(eventInfo.GetSchoolMask()))
1575 {
1576 case SPELL_SCHOOL_HOLY:
1577 spellId = SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_HOLY;
1578 break;
1579 case SPELL_SCHOOL_FIRE:
1580 spellId = SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_FIRE;
1581 break;
1582 case SPELL_SCHOOL_NATURE:
1583 spellId = SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_NATURE;
1584 break;
1585 case SPELL_SCHOOL_FROST:
1586 spellId = SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_FROST;
1587 break;
1588 case SPELL_SCHOOL_SHADOW:
1589 spellId = SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_SHADOW;
1590 break;
1591 case SPELL_SCHOOL_ARCANE:
1592 spellId = SPELL_GEN_OBSIDIAN_ARMOR_ARCANE;
1593 break;
1594 default:
1595 return;
1596 }
1597 GetTarget()->CastSpell(GetTarget(), spellId, true, nullptr, aurEff);
1598 }
1599
1600 void Register() override
1601 {
1602 DoCheckProc += AuraCheckProcFn(spell_gen_obsidian_armor::CheckProc);
1603 OnEffectProc += AuraEffectProcFn(spell_gen_obsidian_armor::OnProc, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY);
1604 }

1639// 6962 - Pet Summoned
1640class spell_gen_pet_summoned : public SpellScript
1641{
1642 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_pet_summoned);
1643
1644 bool Load() override
1645 {
1646 return GetCaster()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER;
1647 }
1648
1649 void HandleScript(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
1650 {
1651 Player* player = GetCaster()->ToPlayer();
1652 if (player->GetLastPetNumber() && player->CanResummonPet(player->GetLastPetSpell()))
1653 {
1654 PetType newPetType = (player->getClass() == CLASS_HUNTER) ? HUNTER_PET : SUMMON_PET;
1655 Pet* newPet = new Pet(player, newPetType);
1656 if (newPet->LoadPetFromDB(player, 0, player->GetLastPetNumber(), true, 100))
1657 {
1658 newPet->SetPower(newPet->getPowerType(), newPet->GetMaxPower(newPet->getPowerType()));
1659
1660 switch (newPet->GetEntry())
1661 {
1662 case NPC_DOOMGUARD:
1663 case NPC_INFERNAL:
1664 newPet->SetEntry(NPC_IMP);
1665 break;
1666 default:
1667 break;
1668 }
1669 }
1670 else
1671 delete newPet;
1672 }
1673 }
1674
1675 void Register() override
1676 {
1677 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_pet_summoned::HandleScript, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
1678 }

1790 target->ToCreature()->SetReactState(REACT_AGGRESSIVE);
1791 }

1837enum PvPTrinketTriggeredSpells
1838{
1839 SPELL_WILL_OF_THE_FORSAKEN_COOLDOWN_TRIGGER = 72752,
1840 SPELL_WILL_OF_THE_FORSAKEN_COOLDOWN_TRIGGER_WOTF = 72757,
1841 SPELL_PVP_TRINKET = 42292,
1842};
1843
1844/* 72752 - Will of the Forsaken Cooldown Trigger
1845 72757 - Will of the Forsaken Cooldown Trigger (WOTF) */
1846class spell_pvp_trinket_wotf_shared_cd : public SpellScript
1847{
1848 PrepareSpellScript(spell_pvp_trinket_wotf_shared_cd);
1849
1850 bool Load() override
1851 {
1852 return GetCaster()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER;
1853 }
1854
1855 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellEntry*/) override
1856 {
1857 return ValidateSpellInfo({
1858 SPELL_WILL_OF_THE_FORSAKEN_COOLDOWN_TRIGGER,
1859 SPELL_WILL_OF_THE_FORSAKEN_COOLDOWN_TRIGGER_WOTF,
1860 SPELL_PVP_TRINKET });
1861 }
1862
1863 void HandleScript()
1864 {
1865 Player* player = GetCaster()->ToPlayer();
1866 // This is only needed because spells cast from spell_linked_spell are triggered by default
1867 // Spell::SendSpellCooldown() skips all spells with TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SPELL_AND_CATEGORY_CD
1868 player->AddSpellAndCategoryCooldowns(GetSpellInfo(), GetCastItem() ? GetCastItem()->GetEntry() : 0, GetSpell());
1869
1870 if (player->GetTeamId(true) == TEAM_HORDE)
1871 {
1872 if (GetSpellInfo()->Id == SPELL_WILL_OF_THE_FORSAKEN_COOLDOWN_TRIGGER)
1873 {
1874 WorldPacket data;
1875 player->BuildCooldownPacket(data, SPELL_COOLDOWN_FLAG_INCLUDE_GCD, 7744, GetSpellInfo()->CategoryRecoveryTime); // Will of the forsaken
1876 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
1877 }
1878 else
1879 {
1880 WorldPacket data(SMSG_INITIAL_SPELLS, (1 + 2 + 2 + 4 + 2 + 2 + 4 + 4));
1881 data << uint8(0);
1882 data << uint16(0);
1883 data << uint16(1);
1884 data << uint32(42292); // PvP Trinket spell
1885 data << uint16(0); // cast item id
1886 data << uint16(GetSpellInfo()->GetCategory()); // spell category
1887 data << uint32(0);
1888 data << uint32(GetSpellInfo()->CategoryRecoveryTime);
1889 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
1890
1891 WorldPacket data2;
1892 player->BuildCooldownPacket(data2, SPELL_COOLDOWN_FLAG_INCLUDE_GCD, SPELL_PVP_TRINKET, GetSpellInfo()->CategoryRecoveryTime); // PvP Trinket spell
1893 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data2);
1894 }
1895 }
1896 }
1897
1898 void Register() override
1899 {
1900 AfterCast += SpellCastFn(spell_pvp_trinket_wotf_shared_cd::HandleScript);
1901 }
1902};

1923 // Remove all auras with spell id 46221, except the one currently being applied
1924 while (Aura* aur = GetUnitOwner()->GetOwnedAura(SPELL_ANIMAL_BLOOD, ObjectGuid::Empty, ObjectGuid::Empty, 0, GetAura()))
1925 GetUnitOwner()->RemoveOwnedAura(aur);
1926 }
1927
1928 void OnRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
1929 {
1930 if (Unit* owner = GetUnitOwner())
1931 {
1932 if (owner->IsInWater())
1933 owner->CastSpell(owner, SPELL_SPAWN_BLOOD_POOL, true);
1934 }
1935 }
1936
1937 void Register() override
1938 {
1939 AfterEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_animal_blood::OnApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
1940 AfterEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_animal_blood::OnRemove, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
1941 }

2082/* 41054, 63418 - Copy Weapon
2083 45205 - Copy Offhand Weapon
2084 57594 - Copy Ranged Weapon
2085 69893 - Copy Weapon (No Threat)
2086 69896 - Copy Offhand Weapon (No Threat) */
2087class spell_gen_clone_weapon_aura : public AuraScript
2088{
2089 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_clone_weapon_aura);
2090
2091 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
2092 {
2093 return ValidateSpellInfo(
2094 {
2095 SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_AURA,
2096 SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_2_AURA,
2097 SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_3_AURA,
2098 SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_AURA,
2099 SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_2_AURA,
2100 SPELL_COPY_RANGED_AURA
2101 });
2102 }
2103
2104 bool Load() override
2105 {
2106 prevItem = 0;
2107 return true;
2108 }
2109
2110 void OnApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
2111 {
2112 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2113 Unit* target = GetTarget();
2114 if (!caster)
2115 return;
2116
2117 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
2118 {
2119 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_AURA:
2120 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_2_AURA:
2121 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_3_AURA:
2122 {
2123 prevItem = target->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID);
2124
2125 if (Player* player = caster->ToPlayer())
2126 {
2127 if (Item* mainItem = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND))
2128 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID, mainItem->GetEntry());
2129 }
2130 else
2131 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID, caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID));
2132 break;
2133 }
2134 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_AURA:
2135 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_2_AURA:
2136 {
2137 prevItem = target->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 1);
2138
2139 if (Player* player = caster->ToPlayer())
2140 {
2141 if (Item* offItem = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND))
2142 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 1, offItem->GetEntry());
2143 }
2144 else
2145 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 1, caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 1));
2146 break;
2147 }
2148 case SPELL_COPY_RANGED_AURA:
2149 {
2150 prevItem = target->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 2);
2151
2152 if (Player* player = caster->ToPlayer())
2153 {
2154 if (Item* rangedItem = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED))
2155 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 2, rangedItem->GetEntry());
2156 }
2157 else
2158 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 2, caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 2));
2159 break;
2160 }
2161 default:
2162 break;
2163 }
2164 }
2165
2166 void OnRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
2167 {
2168 Unit* target = GetTarget();
2169
2170 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
2171 {
2172 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_AURA:
2173 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_2_AURA:
2174 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_3_AURA:
2175 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID, prevItem);
2176 break;
2177 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_AURA:
2178 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_2_AURA:
2179 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 1, prevItem);
2180 break;
2181 case SPELL_COPY_RANGED_AURA:
2182 target->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + 2, prevItem);
2183 break;
2184 default:
2185 break;
2186 }
2187 }
2188
2189 void Register() override
2190 {
2191 OnEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_clone_weapon_aura::OnApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK);
2192 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_clone_weapon_aura::OnRemove, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK);
2193 }
2194
2195private:
2196 uint32 prevItem;
2197};

2240// 25281 - Turkey Marker
2241class spell_gen_turkey_marker : public AuraScript
2242{
2243 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_turkey_marker);
2244
2245 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
2246 {
2247 return ValidateSpellInfo({ SPELL_TURKEY_VENGEANCE });
2248 }
2249
2250 bool Load() override
2251 {
2252 _applyTimes.clear();
2253 stackAmount = 0;
2254 return true;
2255 }
2256
2257 void OnPeriodic(AuraEffect const* aurEff)
2258 {
2259 if (GetStackAmount() > stackAmount)
2260 {
2261 _applyTimes.push_back(GameTime::GetGameTimeMS().count());
2262 stackAmount++;
2263 }
2264
2265 // pop stack if it expired for us
2266 if (_applyTimes.front() + GetMaxDuration() < GameTime::GetGameTimeMS().count())
2267 {
2268 stackAmount--;
2269 ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_EXPIRE);
2270 }
2271
2272 // dont cast this spell on every tick
2273 if (stackAmount >= 15 && stackAmount < 40)
2274 {
2275 stackAmount = 40;
2276 GetTarget()->CastSpell(GetTarget(), SPELL_TURKEY_VENGEANCE, true, nullptr, aurEff, GetCasterGUID());
2277 }
2278 }
2279
2280 void Register() override
2281 {
2282 OnEffectPeriodic += AuraEffectPeriodicFn(spell_gen_turkey_marker::OnPeriodic, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY);
2283 }
2284
2285 std::list<uint32> _applyTimes;
2286 int16 stackAmount;
2287};

2354class spell_gen_vehicle_scaling_aura: public AuraScript
2355{
2356 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_vehicle_scaling_aura);
2357
2358 bool Load() override
2359 {
2360 return GetCaster() && GetCaster()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && GetOwner()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT;
2361 }
2362
2363 void CalculateAmount(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
2364 {
2365 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2366 float factor;
2367 uint16 baseItemLevel;
2368
2370 switch (GetId())
2371 {
2372 case SPELL_GEAR_SCALING:
2373 factor = 1.0f;
2374 baseItemLevel = 205;
2375 break;
2376 default:
2377 factor = 1.0f;
2378 baseItemLevel = 170;
2379 break;
2380 }
2381
2382 float avgILvl = caster->ToPlayer()->GetAverageItemLevel();
2383 if (avgILvl < baseItemLevel)
2384 return;
2385
2386 amount = uint16((avgILvl - baseItemLevel) * factor);
2387 }
2388
2389 void Register() override
2390 {
2391 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_gen_vehicle_scaling_aura::CalculateAmount, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT);
2392 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_gen_vehicle_scaling_aura::CalculateAmount, EFFECT_1, SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE);
2393 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_gen_vehicle_scaling_aura::CalculateAmount, EFFECT_2, SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_HEALTH_PERCENT);
2394 }
2395};

2409 void HandleDummy(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
2410 {
2411 Player* player = GetCaster()->ToPlayer();
2412 uint32 factionId = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].CalcValue();
2413 int32 repChange = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[EFFECT_1].CalcValue();
2414
2415 FactionEntry const* factionEntry = sFactionStore.LookupEntry(factionId);
2416
2417 if (!factionEntry)
2418 return;
2419
2420 // Set rep to baserep + basepoints (expecting spillover for oposite faction -> become hated)
2421 // Not when player already has equal or higher rep with this faction
2422 if (player->GetReputationMgr().GetReputation(factionEntry) <= repChange)
2423 player->GetReputationMgr().SetReputation(factionEntry, static_cast<float>(repChange));
2424
2425 // EFFECT_INDEX_2 most likely update at war state, we already handle this in SetReputation
2426 }

2564 SPELL_TRANSPORTER_MALFUNCTION_MISS
2565 });
2566 }

2568 void HandleDummy(SpellEffIndex /* effIndex */)
2569 {
2570 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
2571 int32 r = irand(0, 119);
2572 if (r < 20) // Transporter Malfunction - 1/6 polymorph
2573 caster->CastSpell(caster, SPELL_TRANSPORTER_MALFUNCTION_POLYMORPH, true);
2574 else if (r < 100) // Evil Twin - 4/6 evil twin
2575 caster->CastSpell(caster, SPELL_TRANSPORTER_EVIL_TWIN, true);
2576 else // Transporter Malfunction - 1/6 miss the target
2577 caster->CastSpell(caster, SPELL_TRANSPORTER_MALFUNCTION_MISS, true);
2578 }
2579
2580 void Register() override
2581 {
2582 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_gadgetzan_transporter_backfire::HandleDummy, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY);
2583 }

2648/* 69673 - Silver Covenant Disguise (spell_gen_silver_covenant_disguise)
2649 69672 - Sunreaver Disguise (spell_gen_sunreaver_disguise) */
2650class spell_gen_dalaran_disguise : public SpellScript
2651{
2652 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_dalaran_disguise);
2653
2654 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
2655 {
2656 return ValidateSpellInfo(
2657 {
2658 SPELL_SUNREAVER_DISGUISE_TRIGGER,
2659 SPELL_SUNREAVER_DISGUISE_FEMALE,
2660 SPELL_SUNREAVER_DISGUISE_MALE,
2661 SPELL_SILVER_COVENANT_DISGUISE_TRIGGER,
2662 SPELL_SILVER_COVENANT_DISGUISE_FEMALE,
2663 SPELL_SILVER_COVENANT_DISGUISE_MALE

2668 {

2674

2676 {
2677 case SPELL_SUNREAVER_DISGUISE_TRIGGER:

2679 break;
2680 case SPELL_SILVER_COVENANT_DISGUISE_TRIGGER:
2681 spellId = gender ? SPELL_SILVER_COVENANT_DISGUISE_FEMALE : SPELL_SILVER_COVENANT_DISGUISE_MALE;
2682 break;
2683 default:
2684 break;
2685 }
2686
2687 GetCaster()->CastSpell(player, spellId, true);
2688 }
2689 }

2697/* DOCUMENTATION: Break-Shield spells
2698 Break-Shield spells can be classified in three groups:
2699
2700 - Spells on vehicle bar used by players:
2701 + EFFECT_0: SCRIPT_EFFECT
2702 + EFFECT_1: NONE
2703 + EFFECT_2: NONE
2704 - Spells cast by players triggered by script:
2705 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
2706 + EFFECT_1: SCRIPT_EFFECT
2707 + EFFECT_2: FORCE_CAST
2708 - Spells cast by NPCs on players:
2709 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
2710 + EFFECT_1: SCRIPT_EFFECT
2711 + EFFECT_2: NONE
2712
2713 In the following script we handle the SCRIPT_EFFECT for effIndex EFFECT_0 and EFFECT_1.
2714 - When handling EFFECT_0 we're in the "Spells on vehicle bar used by players" case
2715 and we'll trigger "Spells cast by players triggered by script"
2716 - When handling EFFECT_1 we're in the "Spells cast by players triggered by script"
2717 or "Spells cast by NPCs on players" so we'll search for the first defend layer and drop it.
2718*/
2719
2720enum BreakShieldSpells
2721{
2722 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_2K = 62626,
2723 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_10K = 64590,
2724
2725 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS = 62575, // Also on ToC5 mounts
2726 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_CAMPAING_WARHORSE = 64595,
2727 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_UNK = 66480,
2728 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_SUNDERING_THURST = 63825
2729};
2730
2731/* 62575, 62626, 64342, 64590, 64595, 64686, 65147, 66480, 68504 - Shield-Breaker
2732 63233 - Necrocution
2733 63825 - Sundering Thrust
2734 64507 - Shield-Breaker Counter */
2735class spell_gen_break_shield : public SpellScript
2736{
2737 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_break_shield)
2738
2739 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
2740 {
2741 return ValidateSpellInfo(
2742 {
2743 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_2K,
2744 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_10K,
2745 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS,
2746 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_CAMPAING_WARHORSE,
2747 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_UNK,
2748 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_SUNDERING_THURST
2749 });
2750 }
2751
2752 void HandleScriptEffect(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
2753 {
2754 Unit* target = GetHitUnit();
2755
2756 switch (effIndex)
2757 {
2758 case EFFECT_0: // On spells wich trigger the damaging spell (and also the visual)
2759 {
2760 uint32 spellId;
2761
2762 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
2763 {
2764 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_UNK:
2765 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_CAMPAING_WARHORSE:
2766 spellId = SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_10K;
2767 break;
2768 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS:
2769 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_SUNDERING_THURST:
2770 spellId = SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_2K;
2771 break;
2772 default:
2773 return;
2774 }
2775
2776 if (Unit* rider = GetCaster()->GetCharmer())
2777 rider->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
2778 else
2779 GetCaster()->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
2780 break;
2781 }
2782 case EFFECT_1: // On damaging spells, for removing a defend layer
2783 {
2784 Unit::AuraApplicationMap const& auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
2785 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
2786 {
2787 if (Aura* aura = itr->second->GetBase())
2788 {
2789 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = aura->GetSpellInfo();
2790 if (auraInfo && auraInfo->SpellIconID == 2007 && aura->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN))
2791 {
2792 aura->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
2793 // Remove dummys from rider (Necessary for updating visual shields)
2794 if (Unit* rider = target->GetCharmer())
2795 if (Aura* defend = rider->GetAura(aura->GetId()))
2796 defend->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
2797 break;
2798 }
2799 }
2800 }
2801 break;
2802 }
2803 default:
2804 break;
2805 }
2806 }
2807
2808 void Register() override
2809 {
2810 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_break_shield::HandleScriptEffect, EFFECT_FIRST_FOUND, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
2811 }
2812};
2813
2814/* DOCUMENTATION: Charge spells
2815 Charge spells can be classified in four groups:
2816
2817 - Spells on vehicle bar used by players:
2818 + EFFECT_0: SCRIPT_EFFECT
2819 + EFFECT_1: TRIGGER_SPELL
2820 + EFFECT_2: NONE
2821 - Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script:
2822 + EFFECT_0: CHARGE
2823 + EFFECT_1: TRIGGER_SPELL
2824 + EFFECT_2: APPLY_AURA
2825 - Spells cast by players on the target triggered by script:
2826 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
2827 + EFFECT_1: SCRIPT_EFFECT
2828 + EFFECT_2: NONE
2829 - Spells cast by NPCs on players:
2830 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
2831 + EFFECT_1: CHARGE
2832 + EFFECT_2: SCRIPT_EFFECT
2833
2834 In the following script we handle the SCRIPT_EFFECT and CHARGE
2835 - When handling SCRIPT_EFFECT:
2836 + EFFECT_0: Corresponds to "Spells on vehicle bar used by players" and we make player's mount cast
2837 the charge effect on the current target , "Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script").
2838 + EFFECT_1 and EFFECT_2: Triggered when "Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script" hits target,
2839 corresponding to "Spells cast by players on the target triggered by script" and "Spells cast by
2840 NPCs on players" and we check Defend layers and drop a charge of the first found.
2841 - When handling CHARGE:
2842 + Only launched for "Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script", makes the player cast the
2843 damaging spell on target with a small chance of failing it.
2844*/
2845
2846enum ChargeSpells
2847{
2848 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_8K5 = 62874,
2849 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_20K = 68498,
2850 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_45K = 64591,
2851
2852 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5 = 63661,
2853 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1 = 68284,
2854 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_2 = 68501,
2855 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_1 = 62563,
2856 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_2 = 66481,
2857
2858 SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS = 62960,
2859 SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_TRIAL_CHAMPION = 68282,
2860
2861 SPELL_CHARGE_MISS_EFFECT = 62977,
2862};
2863
2864// 62563, 62874, 62960, 63003, 63010, 63661, 64591, 66481, 68282, 68284, 68321, 68498, 68501 - Charge
2865class spell_gen_mounted_charge : public SpellScript
2866{
2867 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_mounted_charge)
2868
2869 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
2870 {
2871 return ValidateSpellInfo(
2872 {
2873 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_8K5,
2874 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_20K,
2875 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_45K,
2876 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5,
2877 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1,
2878 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_2,
2879 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_1,
2880 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_2,
2881 SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS,
2882 SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_TRIAL_CHAMPION,
2883 SPELL_CHARGE_MISS_EFFECT
2884 });
2885 }
2886
2887 void HandleScriptEffect(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
2888 {
2889 Unit* target = GetHitUnit();
2890
2891 switch (effIndex)
2892 {
2893 case EFFECT_0: // On spells wich trigger the damaging spell (and also the visual)
2894 {
2895 uint32 spellId;
2896
2897 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
2898 {
2899 case SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_TRIAL_CHAMPION:
2900 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1;
2901 break;
2902 case SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS:
2903 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5;
2904 break;
2905 default:
2906 return;
2907 }
2908
2909 // If target isn't a training dummy there's a chance of failing the charge
2910 if (!target->HasUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_DISABLE_MOVE) && roll_chance_f(12.5f))
2911 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_MISS_EFFECT;
2912
2913 if (Unit* vehicle = GetCaster()->GetVehicleBase())
2914 vehicle->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
2915 else
2916 GetCaster()->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
2917 break;
2918 }
2919 case EFFECT_1: // On damaging spells, for removing a defend layer
2920 case EFFECT_2:
2921 {
2922 Unit::AuraApplicationMap const& auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
2923 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
2924 {
2925 if (Aura* aura = itr->second->GetBase())
2926 {
2927 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = aura->GetSpellInfo();
2928 if (auraInfo && auraInfo->SpellIconID == 2007 && aura->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN))
2929 {
2930 aura->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
2931 // Remove dummys from rider (Necessary for updating visual shields)
2932 if (Unit* rider = target->GetCharmer())
2933 if (Aura* defend = rider->GetAura(aura->GetId()))
2934 defend->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
2935 break;
2936 }
2937 }
2938 }
2939 break;
2940 }
2941 }
2942 }
2943
2944 void HandleChargeEffect(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
2945 {
2946 uint32 spellId;
2947
2948 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
2949 {
2950 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5:
2951 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_8K5;
2952 break;
2953 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1:
2954 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_2:
2955 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_20K;
2956 break;
2957 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_1:
2958 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_2:
2959 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_45K;
2960 break;
2961 default:
2962 return;
2963 }
2964
2965 if (Unit* rider = GetCaster()->GetCharmer())
2966 rider->CastSpell(GetHitUnit(), spellId, false);
2967 else
2968 GetCaster()->CastSpell(GetHitUnit(), spellId, false);
2969 }
2970
2971 void Register() override
2972 {
2973 SpellInfo const* spell = sSpellMgr->AssertSpellInfo(m_scriptSpellId);
2974
2975 if (spell->HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT))
2976 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mounted_charge::HandleScriptEffect, EFFECT_FIRST_FOUND, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
2977
2978 if (spell->Effects[EFFECT_0].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_CHARGE)
2979 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mounted_charge::HandleChargeEffect, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_CHARGE);
2980 }
2981};

2983enum DefendVisuals

2990// 62552, 62719, 66482 - Defend
2991class spell_gen_defend : public AuraScript
2992{
2993 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_defend);
2994
2995 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
2996 {
2997 return ValidateSpellInfo(
2998 {
2999 SPELL_VISUAL_SHIELD_1,
3000 SPELL_VISUAL_SHIELD_2,
3001 SPELL_VISUAL_SHIELD_3
3002 });
3003 }
3004
3005 void RefreshVisualShields(AuraEffect const* aurEff, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
3006 {
3007 if (GetCaster())
3008 {
3009 Unit* target = GetTarget();
3010
3011 for (uint8 i = 0; i < GetSpellInfo()->StackAmount; ++i)
3012 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(SPELL_VISUAL_SHIELD_1 + i);
3013
3014 target->CastSpell(target, SPELL_VISUAL_SHIELD_1 + GetAura()->GetStackAmount() - 1, true, nullptr, aurEff);
3015 }
3016 else
3017 GetTarget()->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetId());
3018 }
3019
3020 void RemoveVisualShields(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
3021 {
3022 for (uint8 i = 0; i < GetSpellInfo()->StackAmount; ++i)
3023 GetTarget()->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(SPELL_VISUAL_SHIELD_1 + i);
3024 }
3025
3026 void RemoveDummyFromDriver(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
3027 {
3028 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
3029 if (TempSummon* vehicle = caster->ToTempSummon())
3030 if (Unit* rider = vehicle->GetSummonerUnit())
3031 rider->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetId());
3032 }
3033
3034 void Register() override
3035 {
3036 SpellInfo const* spell = sSpellMgr->AssertSpellInfo(m_scriptSpellId);
3037
3038 // Defend spells cast by NPCs (add visuals)
3039 if (spell->Effects[EFFECT_0].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN)
3040 {
3041 AfterEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_defend::RefreshVisualShields, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK);
3042 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_defend::RemoveVisualShields, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK);
3043 }
3044
3045 // Remove Defend spell from player when he dismounts
3046 if (spell->Effects[EFFECT_2].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN)
3047 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_defend::RemoveDummyFromDriver, EFFECT_2, SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
3048
3049 // Defend spells cast by players (add/remove visuals)
3050 if (spell->Effects[EFFECT_1].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_DUMMY)
3051 {
3052 AfterEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_defend::RefreshVisualShields, EFFECT_1, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK);
3053 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_defend::RemoveVisualShields, EFFECT_1, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_CHANGE_AMOUNT_MASK);
3054 }
3055 }
3056};

3119/* 62774 - Summon Tournament Charger

3142 {
3143 if (GetCaster()->IsInDisallowedMountForm())
3144 GetCaster()->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT);
3145
3146 if (!GetCaster()->HasAura(SPELL_LANCE_EQUIPPED))
3147 {
3148 SetCustomCastResultMessage(SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_MUST_HAVE_LANCE_EQUIPPED);
3149 return SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR;
3150 }
3151
3152 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
3153 }

3505// 61698 - Serverside - Flush - Knockback effect
3506class spell_gen_ds_flush_knockback : public SpellScript
3507{
3508 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_ds_flush_knockback);
3509
3510 void HandleScript(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
3511 {
3512 // Here the target is the water spout and determines the position where the player is knocked from
3513 if (Unit* target = GetHitUnit())
3514 {
3515 if (Player* player = GetCaster()->ToPlayer())
3516 {
3517 float horizontalSpeed = 20.0f + (40.0f - GetCaster()->GetDistance(target));
3518 float verticalSpeed = 8.0f;
3519 // This method relies on the Dalaran Sewer map disposition and Water Spout position
3520 // What we do is knock the player from a position exactly behind him and at the end of the pipe
3521 player->KnockbackFrom(target->GetPositionX(), player->GetPositionY(), horizontalSpeed, verticalSpeed);
3522 }
3523 }
3524 }
3525
3526 void Register() override
3527 {
3528 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_ds_flush_knockback::HandleScript, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY);
3529 }
3530};

3858/* 58983 - Big Blizzard Bear (spell_big_blizzard_bear)
3859 47977 - Magic Broom (spell_magic_broom)
3860 48025 - Headless Horseman's Mount (spell_headless_horseman_mount)
3861 54729 - Winged Steed of the Ebon Blade (spell_winged_steed_of_the_ebon_blade)
3862 71342 - Big Love Rocket (spell_big_love_rocket)
3863 72286 - Invincible (spell_invincible)
3864 74856 - Blazing Hippogryph (spell_blazing_hippogryph)
3865 75614 - Celestial Steed (spell_celestial_steed)
3866 75973 - X-53 Touring Rocket (spell_x53_touring_rocket) */
3867class spell_gen_mount : public SpellScript
3868{
3869 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_mount);
3870
3871public:
3872 spell_gen_mount(uint32 mount0, uint32 mount60, uint32 mount100, uint32 mount150, uint32 mount280, uint32 mount310) : SpellScript(),
3873 _mount0(mount0), _mount60(mount60), _mount100(mount100), _mount150(mount150), _mount280(mount280), _mount310(mount310) { }
3874
3875 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
3876 {
3877 if (_mount0 && !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(_mount0))
3878 return false;
3879 if (_mount60 && !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(_mount60))
3880 return false;
3881 if (_mount100 && !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(_mount100))
3882 return false;
3883 if (_mount150 && !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(_mount150))
3884 return false;
3885 if (_mount280 && !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(_mount280))
3886 return false;
3887 if (_mount310 && !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(_mount310))
3888 return false;
3889 return true;
3890 }
3891
3892 void HandleMount(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
3893 {
3894 PreventHitDefaultEffect(effIndex);
3895
3896 if (Player* target = GetHitPlayer())
3897 {
3898 uint32 petNumber = target->GetTemporaryUnsummonedPetNumber();
3899 target->SetTemporaryUnsummonedPetNumber(0);
3900
3901 // Prevent stacking of mounts and client crashes upon dismounting
3902 target->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED, ObjectGuid::Empty, GetHitAura());
3903
3904 // Triggered spell id dependent on riding skill and zone
3905 bool canFly = false;
3906 uint32 map = GetVirtualMapForMapAndZone(target->GetMapId(), target->GetZoneId());
3907 if (map == 530 || (map == 571 && target->HasSpell(SPELL_COLD_WEATHER_FLYING)))
3908 canFly = true;
3909
3910 AreaTableEntry const* area = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(target->GetAreaId());
3911 // Xinef: add battlefield check
3912 Battlefield* Bf = sBattlefieldMgr->GetBattlefieldToZoneId(target->GetZoneId());
3913 if ((area && canFly && (area->flags & AREA_FLAG_NO_FLY_ZONE)) || (Bf && !Bf->CanFlyIn()))
3914 canFly = false;
3915
3916 uint32 mount = 0;
3917 switch (target->GetBaseSkillValue(SKILL_RIDING))
3918 {
3919 case 0:
3920 mount = _mount0;
3921 break;
3922 case 75:
3923 mount = _mount60;
3924 break;
3925 case 150:
3926 mount = _mount100;
3927 break;
3928 case 225:
3929 if (canFly)
3930 mount = _mount150;
3931 else
3932 mount = _mount100;
3933 break;
3934 case 300:
3935 if (canFly)
3936 {
3937 if (_mount310 && target->Has310Flyer(false))
3938 mount = _mount310;
3939 else
3940 mount = _mount280;
3941 }
3942 else
3943 mount = _mount100;
3944 break;
3945 default:
3946 break;
3947 }
3948
3949 if (mount)
3950 {
3951 PreventHitAura();
3952 target->CastSpell(target, mount, true);
3953 }
3954
3955 if (petNumber)
3956 target->SetTemporaryUnsummonedPetNumber(petNumber);
3957 }
3958 }
3959
3960 void Register() override
3961 {
3962 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mount::HandleMount, EFFECT_2, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
3963 }
3964
3965private:
3966 uint32 _mount0;
3967 uint32 _mount60;
3968 uint32 _mount100;
3969 uint32 _mount150;
3970 uint32 _mount280;
3971 uint32 _mount310;
3972};

4056// 28880, 59542, 59543, 59544, 59545, 59547, 59548 - Gift of the Naaru
4057class spell_gen_gift_of_naaru : public AuraScript
4058{
4059 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_gift_of_naaru);
4060
4061 void CalculateAmount(AuraEffect const* aurEff, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
4062 {
4063 if (!GetCaster())
4064 return;
4065
4066 float heal = 0.0f;
4067 switch (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
4068 {
4069 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
4070 case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
4071 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
4072 heal = 1.885f * float(GetCaster()->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask()));
4073 break;
4074 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
4075 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
4076 heal = std::max(1.885f * float(GetCaster()->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask())), 1.1f * float(GetCaster()->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK)));
4077 break;
4078 case SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR:
4079 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
4080 case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
4081 heal = 1.1f * float(std::max(GetCaster()->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK), GetCaster()->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(RANGED_ATTACK)));
4082 break;
4083 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
4084 default:
4085 break;
4086 }
4087
4088 int32 healTick = floor(heal / aurEff->GetTotalTicks());
4089 amount += int32(std::max(healTick, 0));
4090 }
4091
4092 void Register() override
4093 {
4094 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_gen_gift_of_naaru::CalculateAmount, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL);
4095 }
4096};

4114
4115 void RemoveInvalidTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets)
4116 {
4117 // In arenas Replenishment may only affect the caster
4118 if (Player* caster = GetCaster()->ToPlayer())
4119 {
4120 if (caster->InArena())
4121 {
4122 targets.clear();
4123 targets.push_back(caster);
4124 return;
4125 }
4126 }
4127
4128 targets.remove_if(Acore::PowerCheck(POWER_MANA, false));
4129
4130 uint8 const maxTargets = 10;
4131
4132 if (targets.size() > maxTargets)
4133 {
4134 targets.sort(Acore::PowerPctOrderPred(POWER_MANA));
4135 targets.resize(maxTargets);
4136 }
4137 }
4138
4139 void Register() override
4140 {
4141 OnObjectAreaTargetSelect += SpellObjectAreaTargetSelectFn(spell_gen_replenishment::RemoveInvalidTargets, EFFECT_ALL, TARGET_UNIT_CASTER_AREA_RAID);
4142 }

4261 {

4263 {
4264 return;
4265 }
4266
4267 Unit* u = nullptr;
4268 if (Vehicle* vehicle = GetHitUnit()->GetVehicleKit())
4269 {

4271 vehicle->RemoveAllPassengers();
4272 }
4273 if (u)
4274 u->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(VEHICLE_SPELL_PARACHUTE);
4275 }

4334// Used for some spells cast by vehicles or charmed creatures that do not send a cooldown event on their own.
4335class spell_gen_charmed_unit_spell_cooldown : public SpellScript

4340 {

4342 if (Player* owner = caster->GetCharmerOrOwnerPlayerOrPlayerItself())
4343 {
4344 WorldPacket data;
4345 caster->BuildCooldownPacket(data, SPELL_COOLDOWN_FLAG_NONE, GetSpellInfo()->Id, GetSpellInfo()->RecoveryTime);
4346 owner->SendDirectMessage(&data);
4347 }
4348 }

4350 void Register() override
4351 {
4352 OnCast += SpellCastFn(spell_gen_charmed_unit_spell_cooldown::HandleCast);

4356// 7102 Contagion of Rot
4357class spell_contagion_of_rot : public AuraScript
4358{
4359 PrepareAuraScript(spell_contagion_of_rot);
4360
4361 void OnApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
4362 {
4363 // 7103 => triggered spell that spreads to others
4364 while (Aura* aur = GetUnitOwner()->GetOwnedAura(7103, ObjectGuid::Empty, ObjectGuid::Empty, 0, GetAura()))
4365 {
4366 GetUnitOwner()->RemoveOwnedAura(aur);
4367 }
4368 // 7102 => contagion of rot casted by mobs
4369 while (Aura* aur = GetUnitOwner()->GetOwnedAura(7102, ObjectGuid::Empty, ObjectGuid::Empty, 0, GetAura()))
4370 {
4371 GetUnitOwner()->RemoveOwnedAura(aur);
4372 }
4373 }
4374
4375 void Register() override
4376 {
4377 AfterEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_contagion_of_rot::OnApply, EFFECT_2, SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
4378 }

4484
4485class spell_gen_consume : public AuraScript
4486{
4487 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_consume);
4488
4489public:
4490 spell_gen_consume(uint32 spellId1, uint32 spellId2) : AuraScript(), _spellId1(spellId1), _spellId2(spellId2) { }
4491
4492 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
4493 {
4494 return ValidateSpellInfo({ _spellId1, _spellId2 });
4495 }
4496
4497 void HandleProc(AuraEffect* /*aurEff*/)
4498 {
4499 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
4500 {
4501 if (!caster->IsAlive())
4502 {
4503 GetUnitOwner()->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(GetSpellInfo()->Id);
4504 return;
4505 }
4506
4507 caster->CastSpell(GetUnitOwner(), _spellId1, true);
4508 }
4509 }
4510
4511 void AfterRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
4512 {
4513 if (GetTargetApplication())
4514 {
4515 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
4516 {
4517 if (GetTargetApplication()->GetRemoveMode() == AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEATH)
4518 {
4519 caster->CastSpell(caster, _spellId2, true);
4520 }
4521 else if (GetTargetApplication()->GetRemoveMode() == AURA_REMOVE_BY_EXPIRE)
4522 {
4523 caster->CastSpell(GetTarget(), SPELL_CONSUME_SPIT_OUT, true);
4524 }
4525 }
4526 }
4527 }
4528
4529 void Register() override
4530 {
4531 AfterEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_consume::AfterRemove, EFFECT_1, SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
4532 OnEffectUpdatePeriodic += AuraEffectUpdatePeriodicFn(spell_gen_consume::HandleProc, EFFECT_2, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL);
4533 }
4534
4535private:
4536 uint32 _spellId1;
4537 uint32 _spellId2;
4538};
4539
4540class spell_gen_apply_aura_after_expiration : public AuraScript
4541{
4542 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_apply_aura_after_expiration);
4543
4544public:
4545 spell_gen_apply_aura_after_expiration(uint32 spellId, uint32 effect, uint32 aura) : AuraScript(), _spellId(spellId), _effect(effect), _aura(aura) { }
4546
4547 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
4548 {
4549 return ValidateSpellInfo({ _spellId });
4550 }
4551
4552 void AfterRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
4553 {
4554 if (GetTargetApplication() && GetTargetApplication()->GetRemoveMode() == AURA_REMOVE_BY_EXPIRE)
4555 {
4556 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
4557 {
4558 caster->CastSpell(GetTarget(), _spellId, true);
4559 }
4560 }
4561 }
4562
4563 void Register() override
4564 {
4565 AfterEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_apply_aura_after_expiration::AfterRemove, _effect, _aura, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
4566 }
4567
4568private:
4569 uint32 _spellId;
4570 uint32 _effect;
4571 uint32 _aura;
4572};

4574// 818 Basic Campfire
4575class spell_gen_basic_campfire : public SpellScript
4576{
4577 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_basic_campfire);
4578
4579 void ModDest(SpellDestination& dest)
4580 {
4581 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
4582 {
4583 if (caster->GetMap()->GetGameObjectFloor(caster->GetPhaseMask(), caster->GetPositionX(), caster->GetPositionY(), caster->GetPositionZ()) == -G3D::finf())
4584 {
4585 float ground = caster->GetMap()->GetHeight(dest._position.GetPositionX(), dest._position.GetPositionY(), dest._position.GetPositionZ() + caster->GetCollisionHeight() * 0.5f);
4586 dest._position.m_positionZ = ground;
4587 }
4588 }
4589 }
4590
4591 void Register() override
4592 {
4593 OnDestinationTargetSelect += SpellDestinationTargetSelectFn(spell_gen_basic_campfire::ModDest, EFFECT_0, TARGET_DEST_CASTER_SUMMON);
4594 }
4595};
